  <summary>06/30/1995--Introduced.
Prohibits funds appropriated or otherwise made available for foreign currencies under the Mutual Security Act of 1954 from being available for travel to North Korea unless the President submits to the Congress a certification that North Korea does not have a policy of discriminating, on the basis of national origin or political philosophy, against Members and employees of the Congress in permitting such travel.</summary>
